data.title: Illinois State
data.meta_description: See the most recent Dean's List honorees at ISU. Undergraduates who meet high academic standards are honored each semester by the college of their major.
data.text:
Undergraduates who meet high academic standards, as established by the college of their major, are included in a Dean’s List issued each fall and spring semester. Eligible students must complete 12 or more graded hours during the semester. For more information visit the University Policy and Procedure pages.

Students who chose to restrict access to directory information will not appear on this list.

The Dean's List is updated at the end of each fall and spring term following final grade processing.

Contact the Registrar’s Office if you have questions about your eligibility for making the Dean's List or about Dean's Lists from past terms. Please be aware that graduate students are not eligible for the Dean's List.

Spring Semester 2024
